1
00:00:06,100 --> 00:00:14,360
Subtitles by CJ Entertainment

2
00:00:21,470 --> 00:00:22,690
<i>[4 years ago]
- Where are you?</i>

3
00:00:22,690 --> 00:00:24,940
I just passed Young Wol.

4
00:00:24,940 --> 00:00:26,120
<i>Honey...</i>

5
00:00:26,120 --> 00:00:27,620
What now?

6
00:00:28,440 --> 00:00:31,420
<i>You heading over there is making me nervous for no reason.</i>

7
00:00:31,420 --> 00:00:33,650
Then, should I just quit and go home?

8
00:00:33,650 --> 00:00:35,660
Do I need to chop off my fingers for you to believe me?

9
00:00:35,660 --> 00:00:37,840
<i>Don't say things like that.</i>

10
00:00:37,840 --> 00:00:39,730
<i>Hang on.</i>

11
00:00:39,730 --> 00:00:41,390
<i>Daddy!</i>

12
00:00:41,390 --> 00:00:42,670
Minji!

13
00:00:42,670 --> 00:00:47,620
I'll be home early tomorrow after work so listen to Mom...

14
00:00:47,620 --> 00:00:48,500
Okay?

15
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:49,710
<i>Daddy!</i>

16
00:01:47,480 --> 00:01:50,890
Addict

17
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:16,850
You must want some ice cream.

18
00:03:43,080 --> 00:03:44,120
Minji...

19
00:03:44,940 --> 00:03:46,850
My name is Hyo Jung.

20
00:03:54,690 --> 00:03:58,970
We don't need this!

21
00:05:14,200 --> 00:05:15,260
What?

22
00:05:15,260 --> 00:05:17,570
<i>Hey... go bet for someone.</i>

23
00:05:17,570 --> 00:05:19,280
I told you I'm resting today.

24
00:05:19,280 --> 00:05:21,550
Shut up and hurry.
I'm in a rush.

25
00:05:21,550 --> 00:05:23,240
I think they'll give us some.

26
00:05:24,640 --> 00:05:27,600
<i>Fine, I can get someone else.</i>

27
00:05:29,610 --> 00:05:30,830
What time?

28
00:05:30,830 --> 00:05:34,030
You little... trying to play hard to get.

29
00:05:34,030 --> 00:05:35,860
I'll give you the address, write it down.

30
00:05:35,860 --> 00:05:37,550
What address.

31
00:05:37,550 --> 00:05:39,000
<i>They told us to go to their house.</i>

32
00:06:08,690 --> 00:06:10,030
<i>Who is it?</i>

33
00:06:13,160 --> 00:06:15,500
Did you call for someone?

34
00:06:29,730 --> 00:06:31,590
Mrs. Kwon!

35
00:06:32,120 --> 00:06:34,030
Mrs. Kwon!

36
00:06:34,030 --> 00:06:36,430
Did she forget about morning prayer?

37
00:06:36,430 --> 00:06:38,570
Why is it open?

38
00:06:38,570 --> 00:06:41,530
Mrs. Kwon! Are you home?

39
00:07:13,700 --> 00:07:15,170
<i>Detective Baek.</i>

40
00:07:15,170 --> 00:07:16,280
<i>Come back.</i>

41
00:07:16,280 --> 00:07:18,250
<Quick Mover>
I'm tired of it...

42
00:07:18,250 --> 00:07:20,450
I'm tired of the smell of blood.

43
00:07:20,450 --> 00:07:23,960
I'm tired of feeling sorry for myself in Seoul.

44
00:07:23,960 --> 00:07:26,940
This matches me anyway.

45
00:08:12,470 --> 00:08:13,360
You're a girl?

46
00:08:14,010 --> 00:08:15,780
You can't tell?

47
00:08:17,230 --> 00:08:18,270
You're a student here?

48
00:08:18,270 --> 00:08:19,800
Junior Class, Room 3.

49
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:23,760
Oh, sorry...

50
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:27,050
Sorry, sorry...

51
00:08:32,320 --> 00:08:33,250
What?

52
00:08:33,250 --> 00:08:34,510
<i>An entire family has been murdered.</i>

53
00:08:34,510 --> 00:08:37,510
So what?
Call Flounder.

54
00:08:37,510 --> 00:08:39,760
<i>Senior, you remember Kang Jong Yoon, right?</i>

55
00:08:42,270 --> 00:08:45,620
<i>An entire family was found murdered at Kang Won Do...</i>

56
00:08:45,620 --> 00:08:48,710
<i>...Jung Sun Goon, Shin Won Ri this afternoon.</i>

57
00:08:48,710 --> 00:08:52,650
<i>Mr. Lim, who was murdered the night before, had called Mr. Kang...</i>

58
00:08:52,650 --> 00:08:55,420
<i>...to help place a bet, based on the statements.</i>

59
00:08:55,420 --> 00:08:59,960
<i>Kang killed the family and robbed their house.</i>

60
00:08:59,960 --> 00:09:02,330
<i>The police are currently looking for the fleeing suspect.</i>

61
00:09:02,330 --> 00:09:07,830
<i>Meanwhile, Kang, who stole 2 billion dollars at a casino 4 years ago...</i>

62
00:09:07,830 --> 00:09:11,090
<i>...was last seen wandering around the venues-</i>

63
00:09:15,500 --> 00:09:16,930
- Hey!
- Senior!

64
00:09:16,930 --> 00:09:17,950
Are you sure it's Kang Jong Yoon?

65
00:09:17,950 --> 00:09:19,350
Yes.

66
00:09:19,350 --> 00:09:22,960
Mr. Park had called him into this house the night before the crime.

67
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:26,510
And we confirmed his face with the witness.

68
00:09:30,230 --> 00:09:31,940
Nothing's changed.

69
00:09:33,650 --> 00:09:35,070
This way.

70
00:09:55,760 --> 00:09:57,110
What's wrong with her teeth?

71
00:09:58,010 --> 00:09:58,770
Did she get hit?

72
00:09:58,770 --> 00:10:01,500
You can't break teeth without injuring the mouth.

73
00:10:01,500 --> 00:10:03,240
I think the victim bit something.

74
00:10:04,590 --> 00:10:06,030
He escaped this way.

75
00:10:12,690 --> 00:10:13,820
Victim's identity?

76
00:10:14,190 --> 00:10:15,960
He was a loan shark by the name of Im Do Sool.

77
00:10:15,960 --> 00:10:18,420
It looks like he took all the cash that was in the house.

78
00:10:18,420 --> 00:10:20,780
But, they're looking into the exact amount.

79
00:10:22,420 --> 00:10:24,480
What's our radius search?

80
00:10:24,480 --> 00:10:25,820
20 km.

81
00:10:25,820 --> 00:10:27,310
Make it 40.

82
00:10:27,310 --> 00:10:28,150
Why?

83
00:10:31,030 --> 00:10:33,020
You were in the Army Reserves.
You wouldn't know...

84
00:10:33,060 --> 00:10:35,060
This bastard was in the Marines Special Forces.

85
00:10:35,620 --> 00:10:37,150
Did you send someone over to his house?

86
00:10:39,120 --> 00:10:40,300
H-house?

87
00:10:45,280 --> 00:10:46,970
How long have you been doing this?

88
00:10:49,020 --> 00:10:50,340
Gwang Pal!

89
00:10:51,030 --> 00:10:52,780
Let me ask a favor!

90
00:10:56,500 --> 00:10:59,360
He took his cash, jewels, everything and split.

91
00:10:59,360 --> 00:11:00,160
Bank account?

92
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:01,470
<i>Clean.</i>

93
00:11:01,470 --> 00:11:05,090
He must have been in a rush,
even leaving the dish soap!

94
00:11:05,090 --> 00:11:06,940
Okay. Thank you.

95
00:11:09,080 --> 00:11:11,070
That means he was on the same page.

96
00:11:25,090 --> 00:11:26,730
Everything is set, right?

97
00:11:26,730 --> 00:11:28,960
Who do you think I am?

98
00:11:28,960 --> 00:11:31,310
I told them to call as soon as they see a suspicious guy.

99
00:11:31,310 --> 00:11:33,480
I already told all the merchant ships.

100
00:11:34,270 --> 00:11:37,170
But, is he really coming here?

101
00:11:38,410 --> 00:11:40,570
The thing about gambling addicts...

102
00:11:40,570 --> 00:11:43,180
Instead of killing people...

103
00:11:43,180 --> 00:11:46,280
They care more about gambling.
That's the scary thing.

104
00:11:46,280 --> 00:11:48,400
Their heads go crazy if they think they can't gamble again.

105
00:11:49,520 --> 00:11:54,250
Sooner or later, his wife will be here to bring him money.

106
00:11:55,440 --> 00:11:57,040
This is the only place he can keep gambling.

107
00:11:59,340 --> 00:12:03,700
Is this the bastard I'm thinking of?

108
00:12:06,120 --> 00:12:08,740
The one who screwed you over!

109
00:12:08,740 --> 00:12:11,790
No wonder you're so into it!

110
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:19,680
If I hear that he smuggled out...

111
00:12:19,680 --> 00:12:21,430
You know what'll happen, right?

112
00:12:29,280 --> 00:12:29,890
What?

113
00:12:29,890 --> 00:12:32,010
<i>Senior! We found Kang Jong Yoon's cellphone!</i>

114
00:12:32,010 --> 00:12:32,740
Where?

115
00:12:32,740 --> 00:12:33,780
Young Wol Terminal.

116
00:12:33,780 --> 00:12:34,930
Young Wol?

117
00:12:35,730 --> 00:12:37,200
Young Wol is in the opposite direction!

118
00:12:37,200 --> 00:12:39,900
Is this another mess up?

119
00:13:14,280 --> 00:13:15,030
What?

120
00:13:15,030 --> 00:13:15,960
Senior!

121
00:13:15,960 --> 00:13:17,740
<i>Kang Jong Yoon is inside a bus right now.</i>

122
00:13:17,740 --> 00:13:19,430
<i>He'll be arriving in Won Ju at 1:30.</i>

123
00:13:19,430 --> 00:13:20,530
Won Ju?

124
00:13:30,560 --> 00:13:32,440
Sorry! Sorry!

125
00:13:32,440 --> 00:13:34,090
Hey Baldie! You wanna die?!

126
00:13:34,090 --> 00:13:34,950
Baldie?

127
00:13:34,950 --> 00:13:37,500
Okay! Sorry!

128
00:14:01,980 --> 00:14:04,310
Sorry. Sorry.
This is the police.

129
00:14:04,310 --> 00:14:06,860
Wait! Wait!

130
00:14:58,630 --> 00:15:01,270
<i>Senior! Now!
He turned his phone on!</i>

131
00:15:09,960 --> 00:15:11,790
What are you doing?!

132
00:15:11,790 --> 00:15:13,890
Stay still.
I'll break your arm.

133
00:15:13,890 --> 00:15:15,260
Save me!

134
00:15:20,830 --> 00:15:21,870
Who are you?

135
00:15:22,760 --> 00:15:25,240
I only took $30!

136
00:15:25,240 --> 00:15:28,210
I just needed to make a call once I got here.

137
00:15:34,910 --> 00:15:35,840
What?

138
00:15:35,840 --> 00:15:38,560
<i>We sighted Kang Jong Yoon not too long ago.</i>

139
00:15:38,560 --> 00:15:40,360
What? Where?

140
00:15:40,360 --> 00:15:42,870
He was in... Jung Sun.

141
00:15:42,870 --> 00:15:44,140
Jung Sun?

142
00:17:37,660 --> 00:17:40,400
I really thought that was him.

143
00:17:42,530 --> 00:17:46,520
What kind of crazy man would do that so close to the police station?

144
00:17:49,550 --> 00:17:50,810
What's that?

145
00:17:51,580 --> 00:17:54,940
Im Min Sub, the victim's brother.

146
00:17:55,910 --> 00:17:57,380
Send him off.

147
00:17:57,380 --> 00:17:58,420
Yes.

148
00:17:59,800 --> 00:18:01,180
Excuse me.

149
00:18:01,180 --> 00:18:04,060
You can go back now.
You can't stay here.

150
00:18:04,060 --> 00:18:05,570
We'll contact you later.

151
00:18:06,220 --> 00:18:07,710
Bye.

152
00:18:29,660 --> 00:18:31,540
That's a great photo.

153
00:18:32,230 --> 00:18:34,090
Did you forget that we have a hearing next week?

154
00:18:34,720 --> 00:18:37,180
The Boss decided he wants to be involved.

155
00:18:38,240 --> 00:18:39,460
Regional Unit.

156
00:18:40,600 --> 00:18:43,240
What have you been doing not taking the lead?

157
00:18:43,240 --> 00:18:44,640
I'm sorry.

158
00:18:44,640 --> 00:18:45,970
If you give us a week-

159
00:18:45,970 --> 00:18:47,430
Give us 3 days.

160
00:18:57,120 --> 00:19:01,060
Because he was caught red-handed...

161
00:19:01,060 --> 00:19:03,980
They're wondering how fast we can catch him...

162
00:19:03,980 --> 00:19:05,810
This case is hard as hell but there'll be no reward for catching him.

163
00:19:05,810 --> 00:19:07,460
Is it because of Detective Baek?

164
00:19:09,430 --> 00:19:13,560
The way he murdered the family members still doesn't make sense.

165
00:19:15,350 --> 00:19:16,950
Anyway...

166
00:19:16,950 --> 00:19:21,270
When his kid grows up, this crime will be the most painful for her.

167
00:19:21,270 --> 00:19:26,630
What could be more painful than watching the person you love kill someone?

168
00:19:31,130 --> 00:19:33,300
I shouldn't have said that.

169
00:19:33,990 --> 00:19:35,300
It's fine.

170
00:19:36,750 --> 00:19:39,960
It's more painful to have forgotten the pain.

171
00:19:56,890 --> 00:20:01,530
I can't believe that he was over Jung Sun and didn't run farther away.

172
00:20:01,530 --> 00:20:04,110
What in the world could've gotten into him?

173
00:20:12,020 --> 00:20:13,320
Did Kang Jong Yoon show up?

174
00:20:13,320 --> 00:20:14,750
No!

175
00:20:16,280 --> 00:20:18,080
Then why did you call?

176
00:20:18,080 --> 00:20:22,070
Somebody else came looking for him...

177
00:20:22,070 --> 00:20:23,010
Who was it?

178
00:20:23,010 --> 00:20:25,660
A rough looking guy.

179
00:20:25,660 --> 00:20:27,140
<i>I thought maybe just in case.</i>

180
00:20:27,140 --> 00:20:28,610
Go ahead and write this down.

181
00:20:28,610 --> 00:20:32,760
Silver Grandeur, license number 9881.

182
00:20:32,760 --> 00:20:34,010
Okay.

183
00:20:34,960 --> 00:20:38,640
Search for a Silver Grandeur, license number 9881.

184
00:20:39,440 --> 00:20:40,430
Fine.

185
00:20:53,490 --> 00:20:54,700
Wait.

186
00:20:59,220 --> 00:21:01,750
Go back a little.

187
00:21:03,740 --> 00:21:05,000
Stop.

188
00:21:11,660 --> 00:21:13,470
That's Bong Yang, right?

189
00:21:13,470 --> 00:21:14,290
Yes.

190
00:21:15,920 --> 00:21:18,190
He went inside at 1:22...

191
00:21:19,520 --> 00:21:21,360
...and came out at 1:45.

192
00:22:10,430 --> 00:22:12,200
2 minutes, 57 seconds.

193
00:22:13,410 --> 00:22:16,910
If that took 3 minutes, then that means he was here for 20.

194
00:22:19,160 --> 00:22:22,010
What did that bastard do here?

195
00:22:23,940 --> 00:22:25,600
Where could he have gone?

196
00:22:31,160 --> 00:22:32,700
Have you seen this man?

197
00:22:34,160 --> 00:22:36,150
I've never seen him.

198
00:22:43,740 --> 00:22:45,000
Mrs.!

199
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:46,880
Have you seen this person by any chance?

200
00:22:46,880 --> 00:22:48,410
I'm not a Mrs.

201
00:22:51,330 --> 00:22:54,230
Sorry to bother you but have you seen this person?

202
00:22:54,940 --> 00:22:56,110
I've never seen him.

203
00:22:56,110 --> 00:22:57,320
I'm not sure...

204
00:23:22,820 --> 00:23:25,840
I thought I told you that I've never seen him.

205
00:23:40,930 --> 00:23:42,820
You little...

206
00:23:52,010 --> 00:23:53,110
Found it!

207
00:24:11,600 --> 00:24:14,600
I was hesitant at first.

208
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:24,650
What can you do for me for $500?

209
00:24:24,650 --> 00:24:29,690
In this economy, the question is what can't I do for you.

210
00:24:31,060 --> 00:24:32,350
If...

211
00:24:32,350 --> 00:24:34,840
I wanted to look for someone.

212
00:24:34,840 --> 00:24:35,940
I'm not sure...

213
00:24:37,260 --> 00:24:41,460
I have to renew my contract next month...

214
00:24:57,050 --> 00:25:02,060
I can even look for a stray dog that ran away 10 years ago for you.

215
00:25:02,060 --> 00:25:04,420
Let's see... who are you looking for?

216
00:25:10,230 --> 00:25:12,400
A guy who wants to kill Im Do Sool.

217
00:25:16,590 --> 00:25:19,420
A guy that wants to kill Im Do Sool?

218
00:25:22,360 --> 00:25:24,630
I took the money.

219
00:25:25,670 --> 00:25:26,970
But isn't it funny?

220
00:25:27,860 --> 00:25:30,760
Why was he looking when he's the one who killed him?

221
00:25:38,080 --> 00:25:39,790
What was the suspect's specialty?

222
00:25:40,550 --> 00:25:42,020
Marine.

223
00:25:42,020 --> 00:25:43,750
Do you see something strange?

224
00:25:43,750 --> 00:25:46,300
He stabbed him in the chest 8 times...

225
00:25:46,300 --> 00:25:49,260
But, he completely avoided the body's pressure points.

226
00:25:50,990 --> 00:25:52,250
Could it be a coincidence?

227
00:25:52,250 --> 00:25:55,360
It could be... but there's very little chance of that.

228
00:25:55,360 --> 00:25:57,680
The deepest wound was on the left side of the neck.

229
00:25:57,680 --> 00:26:00,250
This is the only time he stabbed at a pressure point.

230
00:26:02,170 --> 00:26:04,120
He must be a pro.

231
00:26:04,120 --> 00:26:08,980
We found a fiber sample on his neck that matched the daughter's outfit.

232
00:26:09,680 --> 00:26:14,820
He must've killed the daughter first and then the father.

233
00:26:18,890 --> 00:26:21,290
When do you think the wife was killed?

234
00:26:21,290 --> 00:26:23,770
The autopsy isn't complete yet but looking at the muscle contraction,

235
00:26:23,770 --> 00:26:27,410
she was killed 1-2 hours before the other two.

236
00:26:30,110 --> 00:26:33,140
Wife, daughter, victim.

237
00:26:33,720 --> 00:26:35,060
What?

238
00:26:35,060 --> 00:26:37,060
The order that he killed them.

239
00:26:44,640 --> 00:26:47,120
Did I ever thank you for coming?

240
00:26:47,120 --> 00:26:48,210
You did.

241
00:26:55,990 --> 00:27:00,160
Nam Yeh Ri will stay in Seoul and talk to the suspect's family members.

242
00:27:01,520 --> 00:27:02,800
Is anyone there?

243
00:27:05,120 --> 00:27:08,080
Ah... yes...
Hello.

244
00:27:08,080 --> 00:27:10,020
I'm from the police.

245
00:27:10,020 --> 00:27:12,120
You're Kim Eun Joo's nephew, right?

246
00:27:13,180 --> 00:27:16,640
I've broken ties with those people a long time ago.

247
00:27:16,640 --> 00:27:18,200
But! Wait-

248
00:27:19,600 --> 00:27:21,760
I'm here to ask about Kim Eun Joo.

249
00:27:21,760 --> 00:27:24,600
I'm so tired of this!

250
00:27:27,540 --> 00:27:30,610
I have some questions about Kim Eun Joo-

251
00:27:43,100 --> 00:27:44,140
What?

252
00:27:44,140 --> 00:27:45,760
Who the hell is that?

253
00:27:54,590 --> 00:27:55,820
Hey punk!

254
00:27:58,980 --> 00:28:00,430
Senior.

255
00:28:01,570 --> 00:28:02,890
It's been a year.

256
00:28:02,890 --> 00:28:04,400
What are you doing here?

257
00:28:05,810 --> 00:28:07,520
Well...

258
00:28:07,520 --> 00:28:09,520
This case was given to us.

259
00:28:10,950 --> 00:28:13,610
You know...
From above...

260
00:28:16,940 --> 00:28:18,070
And so...

261
00:28:18,740 --> 00:28:20,730
You came here trying to take on the case?

262
00:28:22,150 --> 00:28:23,170
Yes.

263
00:28:27,670 --> 00:28:29,330
Where's Director Yeo?

264
00:28:30,400 --> 00:28:33,070
Encounter

265
00:29:42,520 --> 00:29:45,750
There are blood stains on the wall but not on the frame.

266
00:29:46,870 --> 00:29:50,240
That means the frame wasn't there during the crime.

267
00:29:51,430 --> 00:29:53,640
You're still the same.
Director Yeo.

268
00:29:55,740 --> 00:29:58,530
For a culprit who left his fingerprints everywhere...

269
00:29:58,530 --> 00:30:02,070
Why would he dare to take the frame off and put it back on?

270
00:30:02,070 --> 00:30:04,600
It probably fell during a fight.

271
00:30:04,600 --> 00:30:06,780
Then, what's the motive?

272
00:30:06,780 --> 00:30:10,920
The only thing missing from the scene is a couple of checks and some cash.

273
00:30:10,920 --> 00:30:13,230
